[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     E3 --> D1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     style C1 fill:#9ff,stroke:#333
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     style D3 fill:#ff9,stroke:#333
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     style B4 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon Neptune, Amazon S3, AWS Lambda, Amazon API Gateway, Amazon ElastiCache (Redis), Amazon Comprehend Medical, Amazon EventBridge, AWS KMS |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | Interaction engine Lambda: `neptune-db:ReadDataViaQuery`, `neptune-db:GetQueryStatus` (scoped to cluster ARN). Ingestion Lambdas: `neptune-db:WriteDataViaQuery`, `neptune-db:ReadDataViaQuery`, `s3:GetObject` (source bucket), `comprehend:DetectEntitiesV2`, `comprehend:InferRxNorm`. Normalizer Lambda: `neptune-db:WriteDataViaQuery`, `neptune-db:GetLoaderStatus`. All: `kms:Decrypt`, `kms:GenerateDataKey` (scoped to encryption keys). |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **BAA** | Required. Drug interaction checks are performed in the context of patient care and reference patient medication lists (PHI). |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Encryption** | Neptune: encryption at rest enabled at cluster creation. S3: SSE-KMS for source data and staging buckets. ElastiCache: in-transit and at-rest encryption. All API traffic over TLS 1.2+. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **VPC** | Neptune requires VPC deployment. Lambda functions in same VPC. Security groups: Lambda SG allows outbound to Neptune (8182), ElastiCache (6379), and VPC endpoints (443). Neptune SG allows inbound from Lambda SG on 8182. VPC endpoints: S3 (gateway), Comprehend (interface), CloudWatch Logs (interface), KMS (interface). |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled for all API calls. Neptune audit logging enabled (`neptune_enable_audit_log = 1`). Interaction query logs retained for clinical audit trail (who checked what, when, what was returned). |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Sample Data** | RxNorm: free download from [NLM UMLS](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm/docs/rxnormfiles.html). DrugBank: academic license free, commercial license required for production. FDA SPL: [DailyMed](https://dailymed.nlm.nih.gov/dailymed/spl-resources-all-drug-labels.cfm). MED-RT: free from [VA NDF-RT](https://evs.nci.nih.gov/ftp1/NDF-RT/). |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | Neptune db.r5.large: ~$0.348/hr (~$254/month). Neptune I/O: ~$0.20/million requests. ElastiCache cache.t3.medium: ~$50/month. Comprehend Medical: ~$0.01 per 100 characters (one-time label processing ~$50-100 total). Lambda + API Gateway: negligible at clinical query volumes. Total steady-state: ~$350-400/month for a single-institution deployment. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Service | Role in This Recipe |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |-------------|-------------------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon Neptune | Stores the drug interaction knowledge graph (drugs, enzymes, mechanisms, evidence as nodes and edges) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon S3 | Stages source data files, stores Neptune bulk load CSVs, maintains version history |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Lambda | Runs source parsers, normalization logic, and interaction query engine |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon API Gateway | Exposes REST endpoints for interaction checking |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon Comprehend Medical | Extracts drug entities and relationships from FDA label text |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon ElastiCache (Redis) | Caches interaction query results for common drug combinations |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon EventBridge | Orchestrates scheduled and event-driven ingestion pipeline runs |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS KMS | Manages encryption keys for data at rest and in transit |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Code: Pseudocode Walkthrough
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Step 1: Ingest and Normalize Drug Data from RxNorm
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m RxNorm provides the canonical drug identities that anchor the entire graph. Without normalized drug identifiers, you can't reliably link interaction data from different sources.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m If you skip this step, you'll end up with duplicate drug nodes ("warfarin" and "Coumadin" as separate entities) and miss interactions because the system doesn't know they're the same molecule.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION ingest_rxnorm(rxnorm_file_path):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // RxNorm provides relationships between drug concepts:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // brand names, generic names, ingredients, dose forms, therapeutic classes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     raw_concepts = PARSE_RXNORM_RRF(rxnorm_file_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR EACH concept IN raw_concepts:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Create a node for each drug concept
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         node = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             id: concept.rxcui,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             type: concept.term_type,  // "IN" (ingredient), "BN" (brand), "SCD" (clinical drug)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             name: concept.name,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             tty: concept.term_type,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             suppress: concept.suppress_flag
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         UPSERT_NODE(graph, node)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Load relationships: ingredient-of, tradename-of, has-dose-form
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     relationships = PARSE_RXNORM_RELATIONSHIPS(rxnorm_file_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR EACH rel IN relationships:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         edge = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             from: rel.rxcui_1,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             to: rel.rxcui_2,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             type: rel.relationship_type,  // "has_ingredient", "tradename_of", "isa"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source: "RxNorm",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             version: rel.release_date
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         UPSERT_EDGE(graph, edge)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN count_of_nodes_loaded, count_of_edges_loaded
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Step 2: Load Enzyme and Transporter Relationships from DrugBank
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This step builds the mechanistic layer of the graph. It connects drugs to the enzymes that metabolize them and the transporters that move them. These relationships are the foundation for inferring pharmacokinetic interactions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Without this step, you can only represent interactions as direct drug-drug pairs. You lose the ability to infer new interactions based on shared metabolic pathways.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION ingest_drugbank_mechanisms(drugbank_xml_path):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // DrugBank encodes which enzymes metabolize each drug,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // which transporters carry it, and the nature of the relationship
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     drugs = PARSE_DRUGBANK_XML(drugbank_xml_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR EACH drug IN drugs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Ensure the drug node exists (link to RxNorm via identifier mapping)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         rxcui = LOOKUP_RXCUI(drug.name, drug.cas_number, drug.unii)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF rxcui IS NULL:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             LOG_WARNING("No RxNorm mapping for: " + drug.name)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             CONTINUE
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Load enzyme relationships
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FOR EACH enzyme IN drug.enzymes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             // Create enzyme node if it doesn't exist
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             UPSERT_NODE(graph, {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 id: enzyme.uniprot_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 type: "Enzyme",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 name: enzyme.name,  // e.g., "CYP2C9", "CYP3A4"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 gene: enzyme.gene_name
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             // Create the metabolic relationship edge
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             edge = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 from: rxcui,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 to: enzyme.uniprot_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 type: MAP_ACTION(enzyme.action),  // "SUBSTRATE_OF", "INHIBITS", "INDUCES"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 strength: enzyme.inhibition_strength,  // "strong", "moderate", "weak"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 ki_value: enzyme.ki_nanomolar,  // inhibition constant if available
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 source: "DrugBank",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 evidence: enzyme.references
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             UPSERT_EDGE(graph, edge)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Load transporter relationships (P-glycoprotein, OATP, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FOR EACH transporter IN drug.transporters:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             UPSERT_NODE(graph, {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 id: transporter.uniprot_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 type: "Transporter",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 name: transporter.name,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 gene: transporter.gene_name
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             edge = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 from: rxcui,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 to: transporter.uniprot_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 type: MAP_ACTION(transporter.action),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 source: "DrugBank",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 evidence: transporter.references
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             UPSERT_EDGE(graph, edge)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN count_of_mechanism_edges_loaded
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Step 3: Extract Interactions from FDA Drug Labels
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FDA labels contain interaction information in natural language text. This step uses NLP to extract structured interaction data from label text and convert it into graph edges.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Skipping this step means missing FDA-reviewed interaction information that may not appear in other databases. FDA labels are the authoritative source for US-marketed drugs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION extract_fda_label_interactions(spl_xml_path):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // FDA SPL files contain a "Drug Interactions" section
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // with semi-structured text describing known interactions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     label = PARSE_SPL_XML(spl_xml_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     drug_rxcui = LOOKUP_RXCUI(label.active_ingredient)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     interaction_text = label.sections["drug_interactions"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF interaction_text IS EMPTY:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Use medical NLP to extract drug entities and relationships
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     entities = CALL_MEDICAL_NLP(interaction_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Returns: [{text: "warfarin", type: "MEDICATION", rxcui: "11289"}, ...]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     interactions = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR EACH entity IN entities WHERE entity.type == "MEDICATION":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Extract the context around this entity mention
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         context = GET_SURROUNDING_SENTENCES(interaction_text, entity.offset, window=2)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Classify the interaction from context
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         classification = CLASSIFY_INTERACTION(context)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Returns: {severity, mechanism_type, clinical_effect, management}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         interaction = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             drug_a: drug_rxcui,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             drug_b: entity.rxcui,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             severity: classification.severity,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             mechanism: classification.mechanism_type,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             clinical_effect: classification.clinical_effect,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             management: classification.management,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source: "FDA_SPL",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             label_set_id: label.set_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             effective_date: label.effective_date
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         interactions.APPEND(interaction)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Convert to graph edges
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR EACH interaction IN interactions:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Create a clinical effect node
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         effect_node_id = HASH(interaction.clinical_effect)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         UPSERT_NODE(graph, {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             id: effect_node_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             type: "ClinicalEffect",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             description: interaction.clinical_effect,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             severity: interaction.severity
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Link drugs to effect through mechanism
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         UPSERT_EDGE(graph, {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             from: interaction.drug_a,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             to: effect_node_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             type: "CONTRIBUTES_TO",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             mechanism: interaction.mechanism,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source: "FDA_SPL",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             evidence_level: "Established"  // FDA-reviewed = high confidence
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         UPSERT_EDGE(graph, {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             from: interaction.drug_b,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             to: effect_node_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             type: "CONTRIBUTES_TO",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             mechanism: interaction.mechanism,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source: "FDA_SPL",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             evidence_level: "Established"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN interactions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Step 4: Build the Interaction Query Engine
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This is the core clinical function. Given a list of medications, traverse the graph to find all interaction paths, score them by clinical significance, and return ranked results with explanations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This step is what clinicians actually interact with. If it's too slow (over 500ms), it won't be used in real-time prescribing workflows. If it returns too many low-significance results, clinicians will ignore it entirely.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION check_interactions(medication_list, patient_context):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // medication_list: [{rxcui, dose, frequency, duration}, ...]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // patient_context: {age, weight, renal_function, hepatic_function, genotype}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     interactions_found = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Strategy 1: Direct interaction edges (fastest, catches curated pairs)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR EACH pair IN ALL_PAIRS(medication_list):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         direct = QUERY_GRAPH(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "MATCH (a:Drug {rxcui: $rxcui_a})-[r:INTERACTS_WITH]-(b:Drug {rxcui: $rxcui_b})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m              RETURN r.severity, r.mechanism, r.clinical_effect, r.evidence_level, r.source",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             {rxcui_a: pair[0].rxcui, rxcui_b: pair[1].rxcui}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF direct IS NOT EMPTY:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             interactions_found.APPEND(direct)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Strategy 2: Mechanism-based inference (catches uncurated interactions)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Find drugs that share enzyme/transporter targets
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR EACH drug IN medication_list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         targets = QUERY_GRAPH(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "MATCH (d:Drug {rxcui: $rxcui})-[r]->(t)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m              WHERE t:Enzyme OR t:Transporter
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m              RETURN t.id, t.name, type(r) as relationship, r.strength",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             {rxcui: drug.rxcui}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         drug.targets = targets
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Check for conflicting relationships on shared targets
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR EACH pair IN ALL_PAIRS(medication_list):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         shared_targets = INTERSECT(pair[0].targets, pair[1].targets, by="target_id")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FOR EACH target IN shared_targets:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             rel_a = GET_RELATIONSHIP(pair[0], target)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             rel_b = GET_RELATIONSHIP(pair[1], target)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             // Substrate + Inhibitor = potential interaction
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             IF rel_a.type == "SUBSTRATE_OF" AND rel_b.type == "INHIBITS":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 inferred = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     drug_a: pair[0],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     drug_b: pair[1],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     mechanism: "PK_ENZYME_INHIBITION",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     target: target.name,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     inhibitor_strength: rel_b.strength,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     evidence_level: "Inferred",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     explanation: pair[1].name + " inhibits " + target.name +
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                                  ", which metabolizes " + pair[0].name +
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                                  ". This may increase " + pair[0].name + " levels."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 interactions_found.APPEND(inferred)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             // Substrate + Inducer = potential interaction (opposite direction)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             IF rel_a.type == "SUBSTRATE_OF" AND rel_b.type == "INDUCES":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 inferred = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     drug_a: pair[0],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     drug_b: pair[1],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     mechanism: "PK_ENZYME_INDUCTION",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     target: target.name,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     evidence_level: "Inferred",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     explanation: pair[1].name + " induces " + target.name +
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                                  ", which may decrease " + pair[0].name + " levels."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 interactions_found.APPEND(inferred)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Step 3: Score and contextualize
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     scored_interactions = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR EACH interaction IN interactions_found:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         score = CALCULATE_CLINICAL_SIGNIFICANCE(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             interaction,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             patient_context
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Score considers: mechanism strength, evidence quality,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // patient renal/hepatic function, dose, duration, therapeutic index
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         interaction.score = score
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         interaction.recommendation = GENERATE_RECOMMENDATION(interaction, patient_context)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         scored_interactions.APPEND(interaction)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Sort by clinical significance (highest risk first)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     scored_interactions.SORT_BY(score, DESCENDING)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Filter out interactions below clinical significance threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     significant = FILTER(scored_interactions, WHERE score >= SIGNIFICANCE_THRESHOLD)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         interactions: significant,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         total_checked: LENGTH(ALL_PAIRS(medication_list)),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         total_found: LENGTH(interactions_found),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         total_significant: LENGTH(significant)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Step 5: Cache and Serve Results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Clinical systems need sub-second response times. Caching interaction results for common drug combinations avoids redundant graph traversals while ensuring freshness when the knowledge base updates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION serve_interaction_check(request):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // request: {medications: [...], patient_context: {...}}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Generate cache key from sorted medication RxCUIs
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // (patient context is NOT part of cache key because it varies per patient)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     med_key = SORT(request.medications.map(m => m.rxcui)).JOIN("_")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Check cache for base interaction paths (without patient contextualization)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cached_paths = CACHE_GET("interactions:" + med_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF cached_paths IS NOT NULL:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Re-score cached paths with this patient's context
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         scored = CONTEXTUALIZE(cached_paths, request.patient_context)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN scored
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Cache miss: run full graph traversal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = check_interactions(request.medications, request.patient_context)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Cache the raw interaction paths (before patient-specific scoring)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // TTL aligned with knowledge base update frequency
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     CACHE_SET("interactions:" + med_key, result.raw_paths, TTL=7_DAYS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN result
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Curious how this looks in Python?** The pseudocode above covers the concepts. If you'd like to see sample Python code that demonstrates these patterns using boto3, check out the [Python Example](chapter13.04-python-example). It walks through each step with inline comments and notes on what you'd need to change for a real deployment.
